- Created moderator guides (scripts) that outlined the tasks to be performed while conducting testing, as well as follow up questions, and used likert scales to measure participant responses

- Conducted usability testing to better understand how users interact with our designs and determine problem areas. Responsibilities for testing include: moderating usability sessions, operating recording software, recruiting participants, note-taking, and analyzing data

- Conducted A/B testing to compare and contrast current designs with future designs, and current designs with competitor designs

- Met with and collaborated with designers and project managers on a daily basis to gather insight into designs, establish study requirements, and outline prototype requirements for future usability testing

- Collaborated with other UX researchers and designers to brainstorm and solve various issues that were uncovered during usability testing

- Generated reports using data analysis with key findings from usability studies, and presented them to a team of designers and feature owners

- Provided user interface designers with accessibility advice using WCAG 2.0 as a guide. Also helped establish documentation for future accessibility needs

included.description:
- Conducted accessibility reviews of clients websites using WCAG 2.0 (Web Content Accessibility Guidelines) to identify accessibility issues. Tools used: Morae, Jaws, Colour Contrast Analyzer, and Accessibility Toolbar

- Generated reports that summarized findings from accessibility reviews as well as proposing changes and HTML code that could fix issues.

- Spoke and met with clients to determine the scope of projects as well as communicate status updates on a regular basis

- Participated in usability testing, including by helping develop task scenarios, taking notes, managing recording software, data analysis, and generating reports with key findings and recommendations for changes

- Trained new student interns on how to conduct accessibility reviews, take notes for usability studies, and how to analyze data
